16 (3) An individual shall not knowingly sign more nominating
17 petitions for the same office than there are persons individuals to
18 be elected to the office. An individual who violates this
19 subsection is guilty of a misdemeanor.
20 (4) An individual shall not do any of the following:
21 (a) Sign a nominating petition with a name other than his or
22 her the individual's own name.
23 (b) Make a false statement in a certificate on a nominating
24 petition.
25 (c) If not a circulator, sign a nominating petition as a
26 circulator.
27 (d) Sign a name as circulator other than his or her the
28 individual's own name.
29 (5) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (6), an
