1 individual who violates subsection (4) is guilty of a misdemeanor
2 punishable by a fine of not more than $500.00, or imprisonment for
3 not more than 93 days, or both.
4 (6) An individual shall not sign a nominating petition with
5 multiple names. An individual who violates this subsection is
6 guilty of a felony.
7 (7) If an individual signs a nominating petition in violation
8 of this section, any signature by that individual on the petition
9 is invalid and must not be counted.
10 (8) Instead of filing nominating petitions, a candidate for
11 school board member may pay a nonrefundable filing fee of $100.00
12 to the school district filing official. If this filing fee is paid
13 by the due date for a nominating petition, the payment has the same
14 effect under this section as the filing of a nominating petition.
15 (9) A nominating petition filed under this chapter is subject
16 to the examination and investigation process prescribed in section
17 552 as to its the nominating petition's sufficiency and the
18 validity and genuineness of the signatures on the nominating
19 petition, and to the other procedures prescribed in that section
20 relevant to a nominating petition filed under this chapter.
21 (10) After a nominating petition is filed or filing fee is
22 paid for a candidate for school board member, the candidate is not
23 permitted to withdraw unless a written withdrawal notice, signed by
24 the candidate, is filed with the school district filing official
25 not later than 4 p.m. of the third day after the last day for
26 filing the nominating petition. If the school district filing
27 official is not a county clerk, the school district filing official
28 shall notify the county clerk of the candidates' names and
29 addresses not later than 3 days after the last day for filing a
